title: Lunr - Export as module
body:
This PR exports the `lunr` namespace as a module so that it can be included with `import`.

I'm working on a project with the [`no-var-requires`](https://palantir.github.io/tslint/rules/no-var-requires/) TSLint rule and `moduleResolution: node` in our `tsconfig.json`, so things like `const lunr = require('lunr')` and `import lunr = require('lunr')` are no good. I couldn't find any import statement that both worked and satisfied linter.

FWIW, the Lunr library itself [does export itself as a module](https://github.com/olivernn/lunr.js/blob/20789e26f3732188216d7faf6dafb0a3656f4703/lunr.js#L2040).

title: googlemaps : Use generics in MVCArray (Breaking Change)
body:
**Add generics support to [`MVCArray`](https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/reference#MVCArray).**  
The goal is to keep strong typing in all properties that returns a MVCArray like `Polyline.getPath` 

Example :

```typescript
let path = polyline.getPath();
path.getAt(0).lat();
```

This is a breaking change because of [`HeatMap.getData`](https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/reference#HeatmapLayer) : 

Before :

```typescript
let array = new google.maps.MVCArray();    // still ok after merging
array.setAt(0, 15);
array.setAt(1, 'dummy');

let datas = heatmap.getData(); 
datas.getAt(0).lat(); // Compilation error after merging
```

After :

```typescript
let datas = heatmap.getData<google.maps.LatLng>();
datas.getAt(0).lat();
```

All these properties are affected by this change.

* `Map.controls`
* `Map.overlayMapTypes`
* `Polyline.getPath`
* `Polyline.setPath`
* `PolylineOptions.path`
* `Polygon.getPath`
* `Polygon.getPaths`
* `Polygon.setPath`
* `Polygon.setPaths`
* `PolygonOptions.paths`
* `StreetViewPanorama.controls`
* `geometry.encoding.encodePath`
* `geometry.spherical.computeArea`
* `geometry.spherical.computeLength`
* `geometry.spherical.computeSignedArea`
* `HeatmapLayer.getData`
* `HeatmapLayer.setData`

------

**Test File cleaning**

* Keep the same element id "map" for map container.
* Group and remove duplicate tests on markers
* Change data.addGeoJson({}) which throw errors when executing in browser.
* Change OverlayView which throw errors when executing in browser.
* Add tests on MVCArray and heatmaplayer

I know we're not testing google maps, only the compilation, but I think the maintenance is easier if we could run the test file in browser without exeptions trown during execution.
